div.div: 'parent.relativePath' points at my com.mycompany:MyProject instead of org.apache:apache - Why?

Add an empty to so that it resolves the parent pom from the repositories. org.apache apache (1 more line was trimmed) Here is the relevant doc.
This feature is only for enhancing the development in a local checkout of that project. Set the value to an empty string in case you want to disable the feature and always resolve the parent POM from the repositories.
Default value is: ../pom.xml .
Downloading all maven dependencies to a directory NOT in repository?

The maven dependency plugin can potentially solve your problem. If you have a pom with all your project dependencies specified, all you would need to do is run mvn dependency:copy-dependencies and you will find the target/dependencies folder filled with all the dependencies, including transitive. Adding Gustavo's answer from below: To download the dependency sources, you can use mvn dependency:copy-dependencies -Dclassifier=sources (via Apache Maven Dependency Plugin doc).
